    "My kitchen faucet started leaking on a Thursday night. Not a big deal, right? Just a drip. By Friday morning, the drip was a stream. By Friday evening, the cabinet under the sink was warped and the floor was buckling. I called a plumber — $180 for a weekend visit, $260 for parts and labor. $440 for a leaky faucet. My coworker had the exact same issue. She called her home warranty company. $75. Done by Saturday. Same leak. Same fix. $365 difference. That's when I realized I was doing homeownership the hard way.",
